'''Toyama Shrine''' (十山神社, ''Tōyama Jinja'') is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|12=draft|12=draft}} located in the {{ill|Sonai (Yonaguni)|ja|祖納|12=draft|12=draft}} district of {{ill|Yonaguni, Okinawa|ja|与那国町|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Yaeyama District, Okinawa|ja|八重山郡|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Okinawa Prefecture|ja|沖縄県|12=draft|12=draft}}, Japan.

It is the westernmost shrine in Japan. The shrine is also known by its alternative name, '''Toyama Utaki''' (十山御嶽, ''Toyama Ugan'').

This shrine represents a unique fusion of {{ill|Shinto|ja|神道|12=draft|12=draft}} and the {{ill|Utaki (Okinawa)|ja|御嶽|12=draft|12=draft}} faith of the {{ill|Yaeyama Islands|ja|八重山諸島|12=draft|12=draft}}, maintaining distinctive traditions. The shrine’s annual {{ill|豊年祭|ja|豊年祭|1=Hōnensai|12=draft|12=draft}} (Harvest Festival) is held on {{ill|June 26 (lunar calendar)|ja|6月26日 (旧暦)|12=draft|12=draft}} and includes a sacred {{ill|Tug-of-war|ja|綱引き|12=draft|12=draft}} ritual.
