* {{ill|Sueyoshi-gū|ja|末吉宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sueyoshi-gū|qq=}}}}, and a plan was proposed to develop the local utaki shrines into shrines. This idea was first proposed around 1939, and was featured in a newspaper article on August 27, 1940 (Showa 15) as "One Village, One Company" {{Sfn|加治順人|2018}} .The one village, one shrine concept was initially shelved due to lack of funds, but in 1943 the prefecture applied to the national government for grants to restore the [[eight Ryukyu shrines]]. In addition, five new shrines were designated as prefectural shrines {{Refn|{{ill|Futemma-gū|ja|普天満宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Futemma-gū|qq=}}, {{ill|Sefa-utaki|lt=Saiba Shrine|ja|斎場神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sefa-utaki|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ([[:en:Sefa-utaki|Sefa-utaki]]), {{ill|Nakijin Castle|lt=Hokuzan Shrine|ja|北山神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakijin Castle|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} ([[:en:Nakijin Castle|Nakijin Castle]]), {{ill|Miyako Shrine|ja|宮古神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyako Shrine|qq=}}, and {{ill|Yaeyama Shrine|ja|八重山神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yaeyama Shrine|qq=}} (possibly {{ill|Ōishigaki Utaki|ja|大石垣御嶽|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōishigaki Utaki|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}){{sfn|後田多敦ほか|2020|pp=25-28}} make up the five shrines{{sfn|加治順人|2018|pp=53-55}}.|group=Note}}, and a plan was drawn up to consolidate the more than 900 Utaki shrines into 60 village shrines and 150 subordinate shrines. {{Sfn|加治順人|2018}} Among the utaki that have been converted into shrines are {{ill|Shirogane-do|8=en|10=ja|11=白銀堂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shirogane-do|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} in [[:en:Itoman, Okinawa|Itoman]], {{ill|Tsukishiro-gu Shrine|8=en|10=ja|11=月代宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsukishiro-gu Shrine|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} in